1
00:00:01,161 --> 00:00:02,441
A few months ago,

2
00:00:02,681 --> 00:00:05,241
the Veritas was translated again.

3
00:00:05,321 --> 00:00:07,201
Everyone who worked on the translation

4
00:00:07,281 --> 00:00:09,441
and everyone who subsequently read it

5
00:00:09,521 --> 00:00:10,641
is now dead.

6
00:00:11,001 --> 00:00:12,601
Your tutor's a what?

7
00:00:12,681 --> 00:00:14,081
An alien.

8
00:00:14,161 --> 00:00:15,921
What do you mean, an alien?

9
00:00:16,001 --> 00:00:17,401
A space one.

10
00:00:17,481 --> 00:00:19,721
A space alien.

11
00:00:20,281 --> 00:00:22,841
Will you read the Veritas?

12
00:00:23,281 --> 00:00:26,081
So, you're blind,
and you don't want your enemies to know.

13
00:00:26,481 --> 00:00:27,481
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

14
00:00:27,921 --> 00:00:31,921
(LAUGHS) So your tutor ran
a computer simulation?

15
00:00:32,601 --> 00:00:35,401
Well, more like he got trapped
inside one.

16
00:00:35,481 --> 00:00:37,721
-Can that happen?
-Yeah, he's a alien.

17
00:00:37,801 --> 00:00:39,201
-(CHUCKLES)
-A space one.

18
00:00:39,281 --> 00:00:41,641
(LAUGHS) Yeah, a space one.

19
00:00:42,641 --> 00:00:45,481
Well, let's just call it
a sort of dream.

20
00:00:46,361 --> 00:00:47,921
(PANTING)

21
00:00:50,681 --> 00:00:51,801
(GROWLS)

22
00:00:53,041 --> 00:00:55,641
(LAUGHS) Are you just completely mad?

23
00:00:55,721 --> 00:00:57,961
-Is it working?
-A little bit.

24
00:00:58,441 --> 00:01:00,281
-Not so mad then.
-(LAUGHS)

25
00:01:00,961 --> 00:01:02,921
What are you doing?

26
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:06,321
I'm doing what everybody does
when the world is in danger.

27
00:01:06,401 --> 00:01:07,761
I'm calling the Doctor.

28
00:01:07,841 --> 00:01:09,041
Pressing send.

29
00:01:09,121 --> 00:01:10,521
(GLASSES CHIME)

30
00:01:12,281 --> 00:01:14,921
So this computer simulation
dream thing...

31
00:01:15,161 --> 00:01:16,201
Yeah?

32
00:01:16,281 --> 00:01:17,961
Which, to be clear,
I don't believe a word of.

33
00:01:18,281 --> 00:01:19,761
-Fair enough.
-You said I was in it.

34
00:01:19,841 --> 00:01:20,841
Yeah.

35
00:01:20,921 --> 00:01:23,441
Well, how did it go? The dream version?

36
00:01:23,881 --> 00:01:26,081
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

37
00:01:27,601 --> 00:01:29,241
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

38
00:01:29,441 --> 00:01:32,001
-(BOTH LAUGHING)
-The Pope?

39
00:01:32,081 --> 00:01:34,041
-In person.
-The Pope

40
00:01:34,121 --> 00:01:36,001
-in your flat here.
-Yeah.

41
00:01:36,481 --> 00:01:39,121
-Your tutor has strange dreams.
-I bet he does, you know.

42
00:01:39,601 --> 00:01:42,241
Maybe he's just trying
to keep you on the straight and narrow.

43
00:01:44,041 --> 00:01:45,281
Maybe, yeah.

44
00:01:47,361 --> 00:01:49,241
How do you feel on the subject?

45
00:01:49,921 --> 00:01:51,481
-(DOOR SLAMS OPEN)
-BILL: Whoa!

46
00:01:51,561 --> 00:01:53,001
-(GASPS)
-Stay where you are!

47
00:01:53,081 --> 00:01:54,521
(RAPID BREATHING)

48
00:01:54,601 --> 00:01:56,761
-SOLDIER: Clear!
-Please remain still and calm.

49
00:01:56,841 --> 00:01:58,281
-Sit down.
-Mmm-hmm.

50
00:01:59,641 --> 00:02:01,481
Keep your hands in sight on the table.

51
00:02:01,561 --> 00:02:03,121
-Miss Potts?
-Yeah?

52
00:02:03,201 --> 00:02:04,321
Who is this?

53
00:02:04,401 --> 00:02:06,601
This is my friend Penny.
Who the hell are you?

54
00:02:06,881 --> 00:02:08,601
Room is secure, Your Excellency!

55
00:02:11,201 --> 00:02:13,561
-This is Miss Potts, sir.
-Hi.

56
00:02:13,641 --> 00:02:17,201
Miss Potts, this is
the Secretary-General of the UN.

57
00:02:17,921 --> 00:02:20,761
I have flown here today
to speak to the President.

58
00:02:21,561 --> 00:02:24,361
I'm told you might be able to help.

59
00:02:24,521 --> 00:02:26,081
I don't know the President.

60
00:02:26,681 --> 00:02:28,161
How would I know the President? I mean,

61
00:02:28,241 --> 00:02:31,121
I wouldn't have even voted for him.
He's orange.

62
00:02:31,201 --> 00:02:32,921
I mean, "the" President.

63
00:02:33,441 --> 00:02:34,561
The Doctor.

64
00:02:34,881 --> 00:02:36,361
The Doctor's not a president.

65
00:02:37,481 --> 00:02:38,961
What's he president of?

66
00:02:39,361 --> 00:02:40,561
Well...

67
00:02:41,121 --> 00:02:42,441
In times of crisis,

68
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:45,161
Earth.

69
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:49,001
Is it okay if I get a move on?

70
00:02:51,401 --> 00:02:53,361
BILL: President of the world?

71
00:02:53,441 --> 00:02:55,201
In times of unusual danger,

72
00:02:56,201 --> 00:02:58,641
that status is made official.

73
00:02:59,921 --> 00:03:02,241
Turmezistan, near the border.

74
00:03:02,441 --> 00:03:04,401
This is a disputed area.

75
00:03:04,881 --> 00:03:08,121
A potential hot spot.
The Chinese have troops here.

76
00:03:09,321 --> 00:03:10,881
The Russians here.

77
00:03:11,241 --> 00:03:12,441
The Americans here.

78
00:03:12,521 --> 00:03:14,721
-And in the centre...
-(BEEPING)

79
00:03:14,801 --> 00:03:15,961
A pyramid.

80
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:18,081
Sir? I have Colonel Brabbit on the line.

81
00:03:18,521 --> 00:03:21,041
Colonel Brabbit, you're on
with the Secretary-General.

82
00:03:21,121 --> 00:03:23,681
Colonel, what have you to report?

83
00:03:23,761 --> 00:03:25,801
Nothing, sir. Nothing at all.

84
00:03:26,401 --> 00:03:28,001
It seems dormant.

85
00:03:28,201 --> 00:03:31,161
The Russians and the Chinese are
reporting the same.

86
00:03:31,241 --> 00:03:33,601
Reporting what? What's dormant?

87
00:03:33,681 --> 00:03:37,121
The pyramid.
We're keeping it under observation.

88
00:03:39,521 --> 00:03:40,641
Why? What's it been doing?

89
00:03:40,921 --> 00:03:43,281
-You haven't told her?
-SECRETARY-GENERAL: I haven't, no.

90
00:03:43,361 --> 00:03:45,361
COLONEL BRABBIT:
It's a 5,000-year-old pyramid.

91
00:03:45,441 --> 00:03:46,961
There's one problem with that.

92
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:48,921
One little problem.

93
00:03:50,241 --> 00:03:51,721
Wasn't there yesterday.

94
00:03:59,321 --> 00:04:01,321
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

95
00:04:39,961 --> 00:04:41,761
(GUITAR PLAYING)

96
00:04:43,881 --> 00:04:45,441
The end of your life

97
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,841
has already begun.

98
00:04:51,721 --> 00:04:53,601
There's a last place

99
00:04:53,681 --> 00:04:55,121
you will ever go.

100
00:04:56,081 --> 00:04:58,401
A last store you will ever walk through.

101
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,961
A last sight you will ever see.

102
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:03,401
And every step you ever take

103
00:05:04,121 --> 00:05:05,961
ls moving you closer.

104
00:05:09,121 --> 00:05:10,961
-The end of the world...
-(CAR BEEPS)

105
00:05:11,801 --> 00:05:15,081
DOCTOR: Is a billion,
billion tiny moments.

106
00:05:15,561 --> 00:05:17,881
-Don't shut the door!
-(CRACKING)

107
00:05:17,961 --> 00:05:20,361
-(WOMAN SIGHS)
-DOCTOR: And somewhere,

108
00:05:20,441 --> 00:05:21,961
-unnoticed...
-Sorry.

109
00:05:22,601 --> 00:05:24,561
...In silence or in darkness...

110
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:28,041
-(SIGHS) Damn it.
-...it has already begun.

111
00:05:28,801 --> 00:05:31,481
BILL: (THROUGH DOOR) Are you talking
to yourself in there?

112
00:05:32,521 --> 00:05:34,121
I'm meditating.

113
00:05:34,681 --> 00:05:36,281
Been in there for hours.

114
00:05:36,881 --> 00:05:38,641
I've been trying to talk to you.

115
00:05:38,721 --> 00:05:41,641
-(BANGS ON DOOR)
-Have you double locked this thing?

116
00:05:43,121 --> 00:05:44,921
I'm busy thinking.

117
00:05:45,401 --> 00:05:47,841
-(WHIRRING)
-Excellent. Who needs eyesight?

118
00:05:49,001 --> 00:05:51,121
Those monk creatures I told you about.

119
00:05:51,681 --> 00:05:54,481
If they've model led
every event in human history,

120
00:05:55,201 --> 00:05:56,721
if they've simulated

121
00:05:56,801 --> 00:05:59,601
entire events streamed
from day one till now,

122
00:06:00,761 --> 00:06:02,481
think what they'd know.

123
00:06:03,481 --> 00:06:05,601
Think what they could do with that.

124
00:06:06,721 --> 00:06:08,561
BILL: (THROUGH DOOR) The UN called.

125
00:06:08,881 --> 00:06:10,721
They want you
in Turmezistan immediately.

126
00:06:10,801 --> 00:06:12,041
Tell them no!

127
00:06:15,121 --> 00:06:16,121
Oh.

128
00:06:16,201 --> 00:06:18,201
NARDOLE: They wouldn't
take no for an answer.

129
00:06:21,321 --> 00:06:22,761
How did they get it out of my office?

130
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,201
The windows aren't big enough.

131
00:06:24,281 --> 00:06:27,281
Oh, er, they are now.

132
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,321
Are you gonna ask what's going on?

133
00:06:29,401 --> 00:06:32,081
Last I heard, you were on a date
with Penny. What happened?

134
00:06:32,161 --> 00:06:35,081
Uh, the, uh,
United Nations Secretary-General.

135
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:37,561
-Awesome.
-Nah, that wasn't a metaphor.

136
00:06:37,641 --> 00:06:39,881
Good, because I really
wasn't following it.

137
00:06:39,961 --> 00:06:41,481
SECRETARY-GENERAL: Mr President.

138
00:06:41,561 --> 00:06:43,121
I'm very pleased to see you.

139
00:06:43,401 --> 00:06:46,001
I think we have something of interest.

140
00:06:47,361 --> 00:06:48,561
(WHIRRING)

141
00:06:48,921 --> 00:06:51,161
Why don't you tell me in your own words?

142
00:06:51,841 --> 00:06:53,601
SECRETARY-GENERAL:
It's a matter of a pyramid.

143
00:06:58,841 --> 00:06:59,841
Hello.

144
00:07:01,441 --> 00:07:02,441
Hi.

145
00:07:13,521 --> 00:07:15,801
Oh! You're an angel.

146
00:07:23,001 --> 00:07:26,561
(SCOFFS) You look...
Don't take this the wrong way.

147
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:28,041
You look awful.

148
00:07:28,241 --> 00:07:30,561
How could anyone possibly
take that the wrong way?

149
00:07:30,641 --> 00:07:32,081
(CHUCKLES) Big night last night?

150
00:07:32,881 --> 00:07:33,961
(SIGHS)

151
00:07:34,961 --> 00:07:35,961
There was drinking.

152
00:07:36,241 --> 00:07:38,241
There were breakages.

153
00:07:38,481 --> 00:07:39,481
Textbook.

154
00:07:39,881 --> 00:07:41,521
We're going to stage two today.

155
00:07:41,841 --> 00:07:43,241
Well, it'd be rude not to.

156
00:07:43,321 --> 00:07:44,601
You okay mixing it?

157
00:07:44,681 --> 00:07:46,001
I broke my reading glasses.

158
00:08:05,361 --> 00:08:06,841
(MIST SPRAYING)

159
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:11,521
(MIST SPRAYING)

160
00:08:43,921 --> 00:08:45,841
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

161
00:08:59,961 --> 00:09:01,361
Tell me what you see.

162
00:09:02,201 --> 00:09:03,881
It's a 5,000-year-old pyramid.

163
00:09:04,401 --> 00:09:06,161
-(WHIRRING)
-DOCTOR: What do you know?

164
00:09:06,241 --> 00:09:07,841
It wasn't there yesterday.

165
00:09:07,921 --> 00:09:09,041
Therefore?

166
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:12,721
It's not really a pyramid.

167
00:09:12,801 --> 00:09:15,521
It's something disquised
as a pyramid that

168
00:09:16,121 --> 00:09:17,481
just appeared out of thin air.

169
00:09:17,561 --> 00:09:19,881
And that's all way beyond
human technology

170
00:09:19,961 --> 00:09:22,201
so it's gotta be alien.
It's an alien spaceship.

171
00:09:22,281 --> 00:09:23,641
DOCTOR: There you go.

172
00:09:23,721 --> 00:09:24,921
And what's it doing?

173
00:09:25,001 --> 00:09:27,881
It could've chosen anywhere
on this planet. It chose to sit

174
00:09:27,961 --> 00:09:31,921
on the strategic intersection of
the three most powerful armies on Earth.

175
00:09:32,001 --> 00:09:33,881
So what it's doing, Colonel,

176
00:09:35,201 --> 00:09:37,601
-is sending us a message.
-What message?

177
00:09:38,281 --> 00:09:39,361
Bring it.

178
00:09:42,841 --> 00:09:44,001
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

179
00:09:47,961 --> 00:09:50,201
-Mr President...
-Sir? What are you doing?

180
00:09:50,281 --> 00:09:51,281
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

181
00:09:53,641 --> 00:09:54,681
Bringing it.

182
00:09:55,801 --> 00:09:57,001
Nardole. (BEEPS)

183
00:09:57,961 --> 00:09:59,401
(BEEPS) On it, sir.

184
00:10:00,441 --> 00:10:01,761
What's he doing?

185
00:10:02,321 --> 00:10:04,761
We don't know what the thing
is capable of.

186
00:10:06,561 --> 00:10:07,681
(WHIRRING)

187
00:10:12,001 --> 00:10:13,161
Nothing yet.

188
00:10:13,401 --> 00:10:14,681
All looks fine.

189
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:16,961
What are you doing?

190
00:10:17,961 --> 00:10:19,321
Oh, updating him.

191
00:10:34,761 --> 00:10:35,801
(STONE SCRAPING)

192
00:10:37,961 --> 00:10:39,201
There's something happening, sir.

193
00:10:40,561 --> 00:10:41,921
It's opening up, sir.

194
00:10:42,001 --> 00:10:43,681
There's a door.

195
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:47,201
Nardole?

196
00:10:48,161 --> 00:10:49,601
Something's coming out, sir.

197
00:10:54,281 --> 00:10:56,641
Going by the description you gave me
from the simulation, sir,

198
00:10:56,721 --> 00:10:59,001
I think that's
one of the monk creatures.

199
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:00,361
Hello?

200
00:11:00,841 --> 00:11:02,321
We know you.

201
00:11:02,401 --> 00:11:04,921
Then you'll know
that there is a line in the sand.

202
00:11:05,201 --> 00:11:07,441
And I'm the man on the other side of it.

203
00:11:07,761 --> 00:11:09,121
You wanna keep me that way.

204
00:11:09,201 --> 00:11:12,481
We will take this planet and its people.

205
00:11:12,561 --> 00:11:14,801
You will be prevented.
You will be fought.

206
00:11:14,881 --> 00:11:16,841
We will be invited.

207
00:11:17,721 --> 00:11:21,881
We will take this world.
We will rule its people.

208
00:11:21,961 --> 00:11:24,961
But only when we're asked.

209
00:11:26,281 --> 00:11:28,801
-We will talk again.
-When?

210
00:11:29,561 --> 00:11:31,441
At the end of the Earth.

211
00:11:32,401 --> 00:11:34,281
(STONE SCRAPING)

212
00:11:36,201 --> 00:11:37,241
(WHIRRING)

213
00:11:39,481 --> 00:11:41,481
(MOBILES RINGING)

214
00:11:44,201 --> 00:11:46,281
-COLONEL BRABBIT: 11:57...
-P.M.

215
00:11:46,641 --> 00:11:47,961
Yeah, mine too.

216
00:11:48,161 --> 00:11:49,361
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

217
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,441
It's everyone's.

218
00:11:52,521 --> 00:11:54,321
11:57 p.m.

219
00:11:54,441 --> 00:11:55,521
(WHIRRING)

220
00:11:56,361 --> 00:11:57,401
NARDOLE: Did you get that, sir?

221
00:11:57,481 --> 00:11:59,761
Everyone's phones gone to 11:57.

222
00:12:00,001 --> 00:12:01,441
Yup. Same here.

223
00:12:01,641 --> 00:12:02,801
What's...

224
00:12:03,081 --> 00:12:05,601
-(BEEPS)
-What does that mean, 11:577

225
00:12:05,681 --> 00:12:08,841
Also known as,
three minutes to midnight.

226
00:12:09,121 --> 00:12:10,481
The Doomsday Clock.

227
00:12:10,761 --> 00:12:13,161
-The what?
-Symbolic clock face.

228
00:12:13,241 --> 00:12:16,721
Representing a countdown
to possible global catastrophes

229
00:12:16,801 --> 00:12:19,761
started by some atomic scientists
in 1947.

230
00:12:20,401 --> 00:12:22,041
The closer they set
the clock to midnight,

231
00:12:22,121 --> 00:12:24,921
the closer we are to global disaster.

232
00:12:25,401 --> 00:12:27,001
Currently it's set

233
00:12:27,281 --> 00:12:28,721
at three minutes to midnight.

234
00:12:29,201 --> 00:12:32,881
So now, every clock in the world
is the Doomsday Clock.

235
00:12:33,241 --> 00:12:35,601
-Thanks to the Monks, yes.
-Is this a threat?

236
00:12:35,681 --> 00:12:37,321
I wish it was. Did I tell you?

237
00:12:37,401 --> 00:12:39,921
See, I think this is a warning.

238
00:12:40,121 --> 00:12:43,121
Somewhere, somehow,

239
00:12:44,201 --> 00:12:45,361
the end has begun.

240
00:12:59,601 --> 00:13:00,761
(SIGHS)

241
00:13:03,641 --> 00:13:04,681
(BEEPING)

242
00:13:10,841 --> 00:13:11,921
Fully automated.

243
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:14,041
Lunch?

244
00:13:14,721 --> 00:13:16,121
Well, it'd be rude not to.

245
00:13:28,761 --> 00:13:29,961
(MOBILE RINGING)

246
00:13:30,481 --> 00:13:32,441
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

247
00:13:34,521 --> 00:13:35,801
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

248
00:13:37,121 --> 00:13:38,601
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

249
00:13:38,881 --> 00:13:40,241
(TARDIS STOPS)

250
00:13:41,361 --> 00:13:43,401
-Hello. Privet.
-Ah?

251
00:13:43,921 --> 00:13:46,921
Sorry about that. Needed the call
to zero in on your coordinates.

252
00:13:47,001 --> 00:13:51,121
Now, this is the Secretary-General
of the UN.

253
00:13:51,441 --> 00:13:53,841
I am the President of the world.

254
00:13:54,321 --> 00:13:56,841
And this is Xiaglian.

255
00:13:57,441 --> 00:13:59,561
She's in charge of the Chinese Army.

256
00:14:00,281 --> 00:14:01,921
Say hi to each other.

257
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:05,801
Now, we've been having a bit of a chat.

258
00:14:05,921 --> 00:14:08,041
Thing is, World War Three.

259
00:14:08,441 --> 00:14:10,881
What do you think?
Basically, we're against it.

260
00:14:12,961 --> 00:14:14,321
DOCTOR: Listen to me.

261
00:14:14,801 --> 00:14:17,201
Those creatures in that pyramid,
they have studied your species,

262
00:14:17,281 --> 00:14:18,281
your civilisation.

263
00:14:18,361 --> 00:14:19,841
Your entire history.

264
00:14:20,121 --> 00:14:21,481
They've run a computer simulation
of this world

265
00:14:21,561 --> 00:14:24,401
since you lot first slopped
out of the ocean looking for a fight,

266
00:14:24,481 --> 00:14:28,921
and they have chosen this exact moment
and this exact place to arrive.

267
00:14:29,001 --> 00:14:30,081
Why?

268
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,601
BILL: Because a war is
about to break out.

269
00:14:32,961 --> 00:14:34,081
Possibly.

270
00:14:35,281 --> 00:14:36,641
But whatever it is,

271
00:14:37,281 --> 00:14:39,561
they're right here, right now,

272
00:14:39,881 --> 00:14:42,241
because they believe humanity

273
00:14:42,601 --> 00:14:44,001
will be at its weakest.

274
00:14:44,561 --> 00:14:46,521
Then we'll demonstrate strength.

275
00:14:46,961 --> 00:14:48,361
We will attack the pyramid.

276
00:14:48,441 --> 00:14:50,441
Force is never the answer.

277
00:14:50,521 --> 00:14:52,201
Isn't that right, Doctor?

278
00:14:55,001 --> 00:14:57,201
Contact your masters.
Coordinate your attacks.

279
00:14:57,721 --> 00:14:58,801
Doctor?

280
00:14:58,881 --> 00:15:00,241
I doubt you'll even scratch that thing.

281
00:15:00,321 --> 00:15:02,361
But if you demonstrate
strength and unity,

282
00:15:02,641 --> 00:15:05,401
they might choose to step away.
Bill, take that look off your face.

283
00:15:06,441 --> 00:15:07,441
There's no look on my face.

284
00:15:07,521 --> 00:15:10,001
They did not come here in peace.
We have to do what we can.

285
00:15:10,081 --> 00:15:11,881
Yeah, I get it.

286
00:15:12,121 --> 00:15:13,641
(MOBILES RINGING)

287
00:15:20,121 --> 00:15:21,761
It's two minutes to now.

288
00:15:22,441 --> 00:15:24,041
The Doomsday Clock is moving.

289
00:15:24,401 --> 00:15:25,401
What do we do?

290
00:15:25,641 --> 00:15:27,361
Coordinate your attacks.

291
00:15:40,401 --> 00:15:41,721
What's wrong with him?

292
00:15:43,481 --> 00:15:44,881
What's wrong with the Doctor?

293
00:16:02,961 --> 00:16:05,241
Did Nardole send you to speak with me?

294
00:16:05,721 --> 00:16:07,041
Mighta done.

295
00:16:07,121 --> 00:16:09,521
Mighta said there was something
you want to tell me.

296
00:16:12,081 --> 00:16:13,881
Funny thing, fear, isn't it?

297
00:16:18,961 --> 00:16:20,201
Once it rules you,

298
00:16:21,241 --> 00:16:23,641
you're even afraid
to admit what's scaring you.

299
00:16:23,721 --> 00:16:26,801
For the record, I for one,
fully understand my weakness.

300
00:16:28,081 --> 00:16:29,361
(LOUD BOOM)

301
00:16:29,441 --> 00:16:31,041
Oh, God, what's that?

302
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:52,201
PILOT: Approaching target.
Permission to strike.

303
00:16:53,441 --> 00:16:55,561
BILL: So, why's the pyramid active now?

304
00:16:55,641 --> 00:16:57,761
DOCTOR: Possibly they know
they're about to be bombed.

305
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:04,601
PILOT: Target distance 10 miles.
Set position five degrees.

306
00:17:14,321 --> 00:17:15,561
(BUZZING)

307
00:17:18,801 --> 00:17:20,481
(GROWLS)

308
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,361
PILOT: Code 72. Mayday. Mayday!

309
00:17:56,441 --> 00:17:59,641
It's the Monks.
They've hijacked the plane.

310
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:01,641
How did they do that?

311
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:19,001
Oh, they're fine. The crew are alive.

312
00:18:20,961 --> 00:18:22,201
Who are those guys?

313
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:24,201
I think they're ours.

314
00:18:24,961 --> 00:18:27,801
-Yours?
-We targeted the pyramid with a missile.

315
00:18:28,721 --> 00:18:29,961
(MISSILE LAUNCHING)

316
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:36,521
(CRASHING)

317
00:18:38,401 --> 00:18:39,681
RUSSIAN OFFICER: From a submarine.

318
00:18:39,921 --> 00:18:42,361
So demonstrating strength
isn't going to help.

319
00:18:45,441 --> 00:18:49,201
MONKS: We are ready to talk.

320
00:18:58,041 --> 00:19:00,481
Why don't you just take
the afternoon off if you feel that bad?

321
00:19:02,761 --> 00:19:04,601
I can't just take the afternoon off.

322
00:19:04,801 --> 00:19:06,801
How 'bout a kip on the floor
under your desk.

323
00:19:07,481 --> 00:19:09,441
Now that's an idea I can get behind.

324
00:19:10,881 --> 00:19:12,201
(SIGHS)

325
00:19:22,121 --> 00:19:24,001
(MIST HISSING)

326
00:19:42,841 --> 00:19:44,361
(WHIRRING)

327
00:19:48,401 --> 00:19:50,161
I mean, this is a trap. Right?

328
00:19:51,441 --> 00:19:52,521
Possibly.

329
00:19:53,161 --> 00:19:54,561
Probably.

330
00:19:56,681 --> 00:19:58,761
And we're just walking into it?

331
00:19:58,841 --> 00:20:02,201
Well, every trap you walk into
Is a chance to learn about your enemies.

332
00:20:02,881 --> 00:20:04,201
Impossible to set a trap

333
00:20:04,281 --> 00:20:06,801
without making a self-portrait
of your own weaknesses.

334
00:20:07,801 --> 00:20:09,041
Great.

335
00:20:09,121 --> 00:20:10,441
Unless it kills us.

336
00:20:11,561 --> 00:20:13,561
Well, you could say that about anything.

337
00:20:22,561 --> 00:20:23,761
(PYRAMID OPENING SHUTS)

338
00:20:31,361 --> 00:20:32,481
(EXHALES)

339
00:20:35,881 --> 00:20:39,161
(EXHALES)
The human race is about to end.

340
00:20:39,241 --> 00:20:42,281
The chain of events
is already in motion.

341
00:20:42,641 --> 00:20:47,481
Life on Earth will cease
by humanity's own hand.

342
00:20:47,841 --> 00:20:49,881
Observe.

343
00:21:08,921 --> 00:21:10,801
DOCTOR: Ah.

344
00:21:11,041 --> 00:21:13,441
The simulation machine
looks a bit different from the outside.

345
00:21:13,521 --> 00:21:15,921
MONK: We are modelling the future.

346
00:21:16,521 --> 00:21:20,601
Each thread is a chain of days
leading to your end.

347
00:21:20,681 --> 00:21:24,441
We can detect
when a catastrophe is about to occur.

348
00:21:24,881 --> 00:21:27,441
-And?
-MONK: Stop it from occurring.

349
00:21:27,721 --> 00:21:29,521
COLONEL BRABBIT: You don't look
much like guardian angels.

350
00:21:29,801 --> 00:21:33,041
MONK: We have chosen
this form to look like you.

351
00:21:33,121 --> 00:21:34,401
COLONEL BRABBIT: You look like corpses.

352
00:21:34,481 --> 00:21:37,561
You are corpses to us.

353
00:21:38,321 --> 00:21:40,041
Your world is ending.

354
00:21:40,121 --> 00:21:41,801
You can do nothing.

355
00:21:41,881 --> 00:21:43,481
But we can save you.

356
00:21:43,561 --> 00:21:44,761
Save us, then.

357
00:21:44,841 --> 00:21:48,041
To save you, we must be asked.

358
00:21:48,361 --> 00:21:49,601
Then what?

359
00:21:49,761 --> 00:21:51,921
We will protect you.

360
00:21:52,321 --> 00:21:54,641
-How long for?
-Forever.

361
00:21:56,841 --> 00:21:58,681
Do you understand now?

362
00:21:59,681 --> 00:22:00,921
Do you see?

363
00:22:01,681 --> 00:22:04,841
Asking them for help has conditions.

364
00:22:06,441 --> 00:22:07,881
Invite them in

365
00:22:08,521 --> 00:22:11,361
and it will be
the last free action you take.

366
00:22:11,441 --> 00:22:16,121
If you do not ask for help
then see the days to come.

367
00:22:16,881 --> 00:22:18,081
(MONK SNARLS)

368
00:22:19,121 --> 00:22:23,761
These are the threads that lead
to one year in your future.

369
00:22:24,281 --> 00:22:27,161
Take them as proof.

370
00:22:35,761 --> 00:22:37,041
(GASPS)

371
00:22:41,081 --> 00:22:42,801
(ALL GROANING)

372
00:22:46,281 --> 00:22:47,281
What was that?

373
00:22:47,641 --> 00:22:49,761
Planet Earth. Not a single living thing.

374
00:22:50,521 --> 00:22:52,001
Dead as the moon.

375
00:22:52,601 --> 00:22:54,321
You seem pretty damn calm about it.

376
00:22:54,961 --> 00:22:56,881
Do I? Oh, I'm sorry.

377
00:22:58,041 --> 00:22:59,761
It's not my first dead planet.

378
00:22:59,841 --> 00:23:03,121
Ask for help. It will be given.

379
00:23:03,201 --> 00:23:06,481
-Why do you need to be asked?
-Power must consent.

380
00:23:06,561 --> 00:23:08,281
"Power must consent.”
What does that mean?

381
00:23:08,361 --> 00:23:11,001
Those who hold power in this world

382
00:23:11,521 --> 00:23:14,281
must consent to our dominion.

383
00:23:15,641 --> 00:23:16,681
Why?

384
00:23:17,441 --> 00:23:19,161
(MOBILES RINGING)

385
00:23:21,841 --> 00:23:23,561
One minute to midnight.

386
00:23:25,081 --> 00:23:27,721
You could take this planet in a...
In a heartbeat.

387
00:23:28,721 --> 00:23:30,161
Why do you need consent?

388
00:23:30,241 --> 00:23:32,001
We must be wanted.

389
00:23:32,481 --> 00:23:34,201
We must be loved.

390
00:23:34,281 --> 00:23:37,841
-To rule through fear is inefficient.
-Of course.

391
00:23:38,241 --> 00:23:40,121
Fear is temporary. Love

392
00:23:40,921 --> 00:23:42,401
is slavery.

393
00:23:43,601 --> 00:23:45,921
If consent is what you need,

394
00:23:46,721 --> 00:23:47,961
I consent now.

395
00:23:48,041 --> 00:23:49,561
No. No.

396
00:23:49,641 --> 00:23:51,321
Don't do this, please.
Don't even consider this...

397
00:23:51,401 --> 00:23:53,201
What I saw is real.

398
00:23:54,081 --> 00:23:55,721
I felt it.

399
00:23:59,481 --> 00:24:00,961
If you can help us,

400
00:24:02,281 --> 00:24:04,041
-I consent.
-Please.

401
00:24:04,561 --> 00:24:05,801
Listen to me.

402
00:24:06,801 --> 00:24:08,361
(WHIRRING)

403
00:24:10,001 --> 00:24:11,921
Do you have power?

404
00:24:12,521 --> 00:24:13,841
I have power.

405
00:24:13,921 --> 00:24:16,081
Does power consent?

406
00:24:16,881 --> 00:24:18,841
Please, stop. Just stop this!

407
00:24:18,921 --> 00:24:21,401
MONK: If your consent is impure,

408
00:24:21,481 --> 00:24:23,401
it will kill you.

409
00:24:24,001 --> 00:24:25,721
DOCTOR: Impure?
What does that mean, impure?

410
00:24:25,801 --> 00:24:27,641
You act out of fear.

411
00:24:28,001 --> 00:24:30,001
Fear is not consent.

412
00:24:30,161 --> 00:24:31,321
(CRIES OUT)

413
00:24:35,561 --> 00:24:36,561
(GASPS)

414
00:24:40,881 --> 00:24:43,001
Planet Earth does not consent
to your help,

415
00:24:43,081 --> 00:24:45,361
your presence, or your conquest.

416
00:24:45,441 --> 00:24:47,521
Thank you for playing
the big pyramid game.

417
00:24:47,601 --> 00:24:49,721
Bye-bye.
See you again next week. Hopefully not.

418
00:24:49,801 --> 00:24:52,841
Without our help,
planet Earth is doomed.

419
00:24:52,921 --> 00:24:55,641
DOCTOR: Yes.
Well, it's been doomed before.

420
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:58,881
Guess what happened? Me.

421
00:25:00,201 --> 00:25:02,081
(GROWLING)

422
00:25:13,001 --> 00:25:15,281
-What are you doing?
-I just need a minute.

423
00:25:15,841 --> 00:25:17,441
I was about to throw up in my suit.

424
00:25:17,681 --> 00:25:18,721
I did that once.

425
00:25:18,801 --> 00:25:19,801
Urgh.

426
00:25:19,921 --> 00:25:21,841
(PLANTS CRACKLING)

427
00:25:29,321 --> 00:25:31,161
Oh, my God.

428
00:25:36,281 --> 00:25:39,801
Okay. Whatever that is,
that is not meant to happen.

429
00:25:41,921 --> 00:25:43,681
We need to sort this.

430
00:25:45,761 --> 00:25:47,921
-(PANEL BEEPING)
-(ROOM DECOMPRESSING)

431
00:25:49,921 --> 00:25:50,921
(DOOR SHUTTING)

432
00:25:51,521 --> 00:25:52,681
(TANK DECOMPRESSING)

433
00:25:56,001 --> 00:25:57,201
(PANEL BEEPING)

434
00:25:59,401 --> 00:26:00,401
(PANEL BEEPING)

435
00:26:04,161 --> 00:26:06,081
COLONEL BRABBIT:
Why do they need consent?

436
00:26:06,161 --> 00:26:07,801
BILL: Maybe they're like vampires.

437
00:26:07,881 --> 00:26:09,721
Can't come in unless they're invited.

438
00:26:09,801 --> 00:26:11,201
They're not vampires.

439
00:26:11,281 --> 00:26:13,641
The future we saw, is it the war?

440
00:26:13,721 --> 00:26:15,841
Do we bring the future?

441
00:26:15,921 --> 00:26:18,481
That would seem to be
the most obvious conclusion.

442
00:26:18,561 --> 00:26:21,081
No! I say no. Friend?

443
00:26:21,761 --> 00:26:23,001
I will not fight you.

444
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:24,521
We are just soldiers in the field.

445
00:26:24,601 --> 00:26:26,401
Are we too afraid to disobey?

446
00:26:27,281 --> 00:26:28,481
I'm not.

447
00:26:33,961 --> 00:26:35,601
Neither am I.

448
00:26:37,601 --> 00:26:38,681
This is amazing.

449
00:26:39,281 --> 00:26:41,361
What do you think, Mr President?

450
00:26:41,921 --> 00:26:44,681
Did we just... Give peace a chance?

451
00:26:48,241 --> 00:26:50,041
The clock.

452
00:26:51,161 --> 00:26:52,361
COLONEL BRABBIT: Sorry?

453
00:26:53,001 --> 00:26:55,401
Look at the clock.

454
00:26:56,081 --> 00:26:57,601
Still one minute to midnight.

455
00:26:58,521 --> 00:27:00,321
It made no difference.

456
00:27:00,401 --> 00:27:02,041
How could this make no difference?

457
00:27:02,121 --> 00:27:04,601
Because it's not you
who's going to end the world.

458
00:27:05,361 --> 00:27:06,561
You were never the problem.

459
00:27:06,721 --> 00:27:07,961
Then who is the problem?

460
00:27:08,041 --> 00:27:10,321
Something is happening somewhere else.

461
00:27:11,161 --> 00:27:13,081
Somewhere in the world.

462
00:27:13,161 --> 00:27:15,201
In silence or in darkness.

463
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:17,761
The world is ending, right now.

464
00:27:18,401 --> 00:27:20,161
And we have to find out where.

465
00:27:24,041 --> 00:27:25,041
It's gone crazy.

466
00:27:25,681 --> 00:27:27,001
It's much too strong.

467
00:27:27,081 --> 00:27:29,121
It's not just breaking
the root system down,

468
00:27:29,201 --> 00:27:30,561
it's killing the whole thing.

469
00:27:31,401 --> 00:27:32,681
We have to seal off the lab.

470
00:27:32,761 --> 00:27:34,521
The greenhouse. Everything.

471
00:27:34,601 --> 00:27:36,641
This can't be allowed
to get into the atmosphere.

472
00:27:43,201 --> 00:27:46,561
This is impossible. We can't search
a whole planet in a few minutes.

473
00:27:46,641 --> 00:27:50,081
Narrow it down. They landed the pyramid
in the middle of a military crisis.

474
00:27:50,161 --> 00:27:51,961
What was the point of that?

475
00:27:53,201 --> 00:27:54,241
Okay, what was the point?

476
00:27:54,321 --> 00:27:58,081
What was the effect?
They told us the world was ending

477
00:27:58,161 --> 00:28:00,041
in a potential war zone.

478
00:28:00,321 --> 00:28:01,881
What did we assume was going to happen?

479
00:28:01,961 --> 00:28:03,001
World War Three.

480
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:05,241
But it didn't.
The trick with misdirection,

481
00:28:05,321 --> 00:28:08,561
don't look where the arrow is pointing.
Look where it's pointing away from.

482
00:28:08,641 --> 00:28:13,961
So, what's already on our radar that
we should be worried about, right now?

483
00:28:14,561 --> 00:28:17,161
Forgot about war.
What else could end the world?

484
00:28:17,241 --> 00:28:19,961
-Bacteria.
-I like the sound of that.

485
00:28:20,041 --> 00:28:22,761
New strain of flu? Plague?

486
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:25,161
People can be immune.
And whatever it is,

487
00:28:25,241 --> 00:28:28,161
it will kill all life on Earth.
Not just humans.

488
00:28:28,681 --> 00:28:30,841
Plague discriminates.

489
00:28:30,921 --> 00:28:33,481
So this isn't a plan. It's a mistake.

490
00:28:33,801 --> 00:28:36,721
Somebody, somewhere, is doing something

491
00:28:36,801 --> 00:28:38,961
that's about to blow up
in everybody's face.

492
00:28:41,921 --> 00:28:43,481
(SCREEN CRACKLING)

493
00:28:48,601 --> 00:28:49,881
What are you doing?

494
00:28:49,961 --> 00:28:52,721
A distraction tells
that whatever's coming

495
00:28:52,801 --> 00:28:55,601
is already on a watch list.

496
00:28:56,721 --> 00:28:59,561
I just put all the top secret
intelligence documents in the world

497
00:28:59,641 --> 00:29:01,521
online, in searchable format!

498
00:29:01,601 --> 00:29:03,881
-What?
-Sit down and Google!

499
00:29:11,881 --> 00:29:13,641
It's never done anything
like that before.

500
00:29:14,281 --> 00:29:15,761
Check the mix.

501
00:29:17,801 --> 00:29:18,881
Anything?

502
00:29:18,961 --> 00:29:20,401
(CHOKING)

503
00:29:20,481 --> 00:29:22,161
Douglas?

504
00:29:22,881 --> 00:29:23,961
Douglas!

505
00:29:25,521 --> 00:29:26,561
Douglas!

506
00:29:26,761 --> 00:29:28,081
(PANTING)

507
00:29:34,361 --> 00:29:36,561
(PANEL BEEPING)

508
00:29:47,321 --> 00:29:49,321
-Doctor, listen.
-What?

509
00:29:49,401 --> 00:29:51,561
Isn't it worth at least
just considering doing the deal?

510
00:29:51,641 --> 00:29:53,921
-What deal?
-All we have to do is consent.

511
00:29:54,001 --> 00:29:56,601
That's what the Secretary-General
thought, and they burned him.

512
00:29:56,681 --> 00:30:00,081
He was afraid.
I'm not being afraid, I'm being smart.

513
00:30:00,161 --> 00:30:03,161
Yeah. Being smart is
not giving away your planet.

514
00:30:03,681 --> 00:30:07,121
So, an accident leading
to irrevocable consequences.

515
00:30:07,201 --> 00:30:08,521
I like bacteria.

516
00:30:09,001 --> 00:30:12,281
They can spread. Once they're out,
you can't put them away again.

517
00:30:12,361 --> 00:30:14,601
What could they do?
What do you depend on?

518
00:30:15,121 --> 00:30:16,841
Air, water, food, beer.

519
00:30:16,921 --> 00:30:20,281
Air, water, and food.
Let's say something's going to change,

520
00:30:20,361 --> 00:30:23,481
something is going to be released.
Something

521
00:30:24,241 --> 00:30:26,601
new, something fast, I'm feeling...

522
00:30:28,161 --> 00:30:29,681
I'm feeling biochemical.

523
00:30:29,761 --> 00:30:32,001
-Check biochemical trials.
-Yes, sir.

524
00:30:32,401 --> 00:30:33,761
Doctor.

525
00:30:34,801 --> 00:30:38,001
That world was dead a year from now.

526
00:30:38,481 --> 00:30:39,881
We should at least go in there and talk.

527
00:30:39,961 --> 00:30:44,401
Well, there are about a hundred thousand
biochemical trials going on right now.

528
00:30:44,481 --> 00:30:47,041
Specifically related to GM bacteria.

529
00:30:47,121 --> 00:30:48,761
Uh, 6,0007?

530
00:30:49,921 --> 00:30:52,481
How many have reached stage two?
You cannot accept their offer.

531
00:30:52,761 --> 00:30:54,281
Why not?

532
00:30:54,361 --> 00:30:56,241
Because whatever the price is,
it's too high.

533
00:30:56,321 --> 00:30:57,321
We'll work it out.

534
00:30:57,401 --> 00:30:58,801
428.

535
00:30:58,881 --> 00:31:01,361
It's too many.
And we don't even know if you're right.

536
00:31:01,441 --> 00:31:02,841
Well, I probably am.

537
00:31:02,921 --> 00:31:04,241
"Probably” isn't good enough.

538
00:31:04,321 --> 00:31:05,841
Well, "probably” is all you have got!

539
00:31:05,921 --> 00:31:07,921
It's your planet,
I can't just give it away.

540
00:31:08,001 --> 00:31:12,001
You know what, sir? Finally
you've said something I agree with.

541
00:31:12,721 --> 00:31:14,321
It's our planet.

542
00:31:14,721 --> 00:31:15,881
Our choice.

543
00:31:15,961 --> 00:31:17,001
You can't make a deal with them.

544
00:31:17,081 --> 00:31:18,881
You don't know what you're agreeing to.
I don't know.

545
00:31:18,961 --> 00:31:22,841
AILLT know is,
I plan on living to fight another day.

546
00:31:23,761 --> 00:31:27,321
Right now, what we don't have
is a whole lot of other days.

547
00:31:27,401 --> 00:31:29,561
-Agreed.
-Also agreed.

548
00:31:30,761 --> 00:31:32,081
Doctor.

549
00:31:35,001 --> 00:31:37,681
Is it just possible that they're right?

550
00:31:39,001 --> 00:31:41,161
Being right is easy. We need to win.

551
00:31:42,601 --> 00:31:45,361
All these soldiers in the room,
and you're the only one still fighting.

552
00:31:45,801 --> 00:31:47,241
Would you make the deal?

553
00:31:47,321 --> 00:31:48,841
Even not knowing what's going to happen?

554
00:31:48,921 --> 00:31:53,441
Those guys have model led every event
in human history, to find our weak spot.

555
00:31:53,801 --> 00:31:55,801
Are you gonna do the same
in a couple of minutes?

556
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:58,081
-Would you make the deal?
-No.

557
00:31:58,161 --> 00:32:00,161
Not if I had a choice.

558
00:32:00,241 --> 00:32:02,401
But we don't. Do we?

559
00:32:02,481 --> 00:32:04,001
It's your world.

560
00:32:04,361 --> 00:32:05,961
Not any more.

561
00:32:08,121 --> 00:32:09,361
Okay.

562
00:32:10,641 --> 00:32:13,641
Back to the pyramid.
And negotiate our surrender.

563
00:32:20,041 --> 00:32:21,041
Doctor.

564
00:32:22,321 --> 00:32:23,321
What are you gonna do?

565
00:32:23,401 --> 00:32:25,121
Well, for a start,
I'm going to tell you the truth.

566
00:32:25,641 --> 00:32:27,761
I've been keeping a secret from you.

567
00:32:34,241 --> 00:32:35,321
BILL: Doctor?

568
00:32:37,401 --> 00:32:40,641
We can blind them. That's how we do it.

569
00:32:41,601 --> 00:32:43,081
We blind them.

570
00:32:43,161 --> 00:32:44,601
Blind who? The Monks?

571
00:32:44,681 --> 00:32:47,201
Bill, go to the pyramid.
Keep an eye on them all.

572
00:32:47,281 --> 00:32:50,081
-Nardole, with me, to the TARDIS!
-Yes, sir.

573
00:32:50,161 --> 00:32:52,041
Have you got a plan?

574
00:32:52,521 --> 00:32:54,401
You'll be hearing from me.

575
00:32:55,321 --> 00:32:57,841
WOMAN: (OVER TANNOY)
Biohazard. Lab in lockdown.

576
00:32:57,921 --> 00:32:58,921
(ALARM BEEPING)

577
00:32:59,001 --> 00:33:01,761
WOMAN: (OVER TANNOY)
Biohazard. Lab in lockdown.

578
00:33:02,881 --> 00:33:05,761
Biohazard. Lab in lockdown.

579
00:33:06,801 --> 00:33:09,561
Biohazard. Lab in lockdown.

580
00:33:10,641 --> 00:33:13,521
Oh, Douglas, what have you done?

581
00:33:14,041 --> 00:33:17,401
Okay, there's a list of labs
on the unit watch list.

582
00:33:17,481 --> 00:33:21,241
If they're being watched, that means
that they've got CCTV cameras

583
00:33:21,321 --> 00:33:24,281
with feeds to Unit 8Q.

584
00:33:24,361 --> 00:33:27,201
-Can you hack them?
-Course I can, I'm not just sexy.

585
00:33:27,281 --> 00:33:30,121
But there's 428 of them,
we can't watch them all.

586
00:33:30,201 --> 00:33:33,361
-Are you following me?
-Yeah, I think I get it.

587
00:33:33,441 --> 00:33:35,001
Yes, well, we're not
going to watch them,

588
00:33:35,081 --> 00:33:36,081
we're going to switch them off,

589
00:33:36,161 --> 00:33:39,081
-can you do that?
-What good would switching them off do?

590
00:33:39,601 --> 00:33:43,601
If I'm right, the Monks are
only watching one of those labs.

591
00:33:43,681 --> 00:33:45,161
How would they do that?

592
00:33:45,241 --> 00:33:48,361
Well, I suppose they'd just...
Hack the cameras!

593
00:33:48,921 --> 00:33:50,321
So switch 'em off.

594
00:33:54,841 --> 00:33:55,841
(MACHINE POWERING OFF)

595
00:33:56,521 --> 00:33:58,921
Okay, so... We've blinded them.

596
00:33:59,361 --> 00:34:01,401
But whatever's happening
is still happening.

597
00:34:01,521 --> 00:34:03,521
-Yup.
-And the Monks are powerful.

598
00:34:03,601 --> 00:34:06,041
They can just turn the cameras back on.

599
00:34:06,121 --> 00:34:07,361
Yes, they can.

600
00:34:07,441 --> 00:34:09,281
But they're only watching one lab.

601
00:34:09,921 --> 00:34:14,121
So all we need to know is
which lab just got its cameras back?

602
00:34:17,361 --> 00:34:19,481
-(MACHINE DINGS)
-Oh, you genius.

603
00:34:20,681 --> 00:34:21,801
Boom.

604
00:34:23,321 --> 00:34:25,441
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

605
00:34:30,681 --> 00:34:31,801
Oh, my God.

606
00:34:31,961 --> 00:34:33,481
No, I'm the Doctor.

607
00:34:33,561 --> 00:34:35,761
But it's an easy mistake to make.
The eyebrows.

608
00:34:35,841 --> 00:34:37,681
How did you do that? What is that thing?

609
00:34:37,761 --> 00:34:39,681
Uh, it's Nardole. He's not my fault.

610
00:34:39,761 --> 00:34:41,721
Back to the TARDIS, this place is toxic.

611
00:34:41,801 --> 00:34:42,841
I'm not human?

612
00:34:42,921 --> 00:34:44,721
Well, you're human enough.
I got your lungs cheap.

613
00:34:44,801 --> 00:34:46,441
Urgh, now he tells me.

614
00:34:46,841 --> 00:34:48,561
Park her close, monitor me.

615
00:34:49,001 --> 00:34:50,601
Oh, tidy up your room?

616
00:34:50,681 --> 00:34:51,681
Urgh.

617
00:34:54,441 --> 00:34:55,761
You have a problem, I believe.

618
00:34:55,841 --> 00:34:57,401
Who the hell are you?

619
00:34:57,481 --> 00:34:58,881
Don't be alarmed, we don't have time.

620
00:34:58,961 --> 00:35:00,401
Just jump straight
to all the explaining.

621
00:35:08,041 --> 00:35:09,521
(COUGHING)

622
00:35:19,681 --> 00:35:21,401
(MOBILE RINGING)

623
00:35:23,161 --> 00:35:24,201
It's the Doctor.

624
00:35:24,281 --> 00:35:27,241
DOCTOR: (OVER PHONE)
Okay, found it. Lab in Yorkshire.

625
00:35:27,321 --> 00:35:28,601
Long story short,

626
00:35:28,681 --> 00:35:31,801
misplaced decimal point
resulting in a bacteria

627
00:35:31,881 --> 00:35:35,041
that turns any living thing it touches
into gunk.

628
00:35:35,281 --> 00:35:38,561
So why is it going to end the world?
Has it been dispersed already?

629
00:35:38,641 --> 00:35:41,761
Uh, no. It's still in the lab.
I think I can contain it.

630
00:35:41,881 --> 00:35:44,761
We give him two minutes,
and we're heading in. Agreed?

631
00:35:45,441 --> 00:35:46,441
Agreed.

632
00:35:47,161 --> 00:35:50,201
We have an air filtration system
to take toxins out of the air.

633
00:35:50,281 --> 00:35:52,281
It runs a cycle every 30 minutes.

634
00:35:52,481 --> 00:35:54,961
It's gonna pump the bacteria
into the atmosphere.

635
00:35:55,041 --> 00:35:57,161
-So switch it off.
-I can't.

636
00:35:57,681 --> 00:36:00,161
Oh. Right, okay. When's the next cycle?

637
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:01,241
Twenty minutes.

638
00:36:01,561 --> 00:36:02,561
What?

639
00:36:03,321 --> 00:36:04,401
(DOCTOR SIGHS)

640
00:36:06,281 --> 00:36:07,281
Anything?

641
00:36:07,361 --> 00:36:08,641
The venting system is automatic.

642
00:36:08,721 --> 00:36:10,161
This is going to be trickier
than I thought.

643
00:36:10,361 --> 00:36:12,241
(ALL PHONES RINGING)

644
00:36:14,121 --> 00:36:15,201
We're going in.

645
00:36:18,441 --> 00:36:20,481
Think, think, think...

646
00:36:20,561 --> 00:36:22,921
Stupid Doctor, stupid, stupid, stupid...

647
00:36:24,441 --> 00:36:27,041
Handsome Doctor!

648
00:36:27,241 --> 00:36:31,521
Adorable, hugely intelligent,
but still approachable Doctor!

649
00:36:34,561 --> 00:36:36,681
What's another way to destroy bacteria?

650
00:36:36,761 --> 00:36:39,121
-Sterilisation.
-And how do you sterilise something?

651
00:36:39,521 --> 00:36:41,041
Put it in boiling water.

652
00:36:41,121 --> 00:36:43,441
-Or?
-Put it in a flame.

653
00:36:44,681 --> 00:36:45,841
She's got it!

654
00:36:47,761 --> 00:36:49,521
By George, she's got it!

655
00:36:49,601 --> 00:36:51,001
I'm not going to lie to you.

656
00:36:51,121 --> 00:36:53,761
This means that your insurance premiums
are going to go through the roof.

657
00:36:53,841 --> 00:36:55,881
In fact, pretty much everything is
going to go through the roof,

658
00:36:55,961 --> 00:36:58,041
because I'm going to blow up the lab.

659
00:36:58,401 --> 00:37:01,081
Just need some kind of a trigger first.

660
00:37:01,161 --> 00:37:03,401
But, what are you going to
blow it up with?

661
00:37:05,001 --> 00:37:07,121
The bacteria is making ethanol.

662
00:37:07,201 --> 00:37:09,001
The greenhouse
and the lab are full of it!

663
00:37:09,081 --> 00:37:11,201
Seriously, what are you doing
when this is all over?

664
00:37:14,401 --> 00:37:15,841
COLONEL BRABBIT: We're ready to talk.

665
00:37:18,761 --> 00:37:20,161
(LOUD BOOM)

666
00:37:23,441 --> 00:37:25,761
Do you have power?

667
00:37:25,841 --> 00:37:30,081
Well, right now we're representing
the three biggest armies on the planet,

668
00:37:30,161 --> 00:37:31,281
so I guess we do.

669
00:37:32,441 --> 00:37:34,281
Does power consent?

670
00:37:35,121 --> 00:37:36,281
We consent.

671
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:40,761
If your consent is impure,
it will kill you.

672
00:37:42,361 --> 00:37:45,321
I surrender. We surrender.

673
00:37:46,001 --> 00:37:47,761
What more do you want?

674
00:37:49,121 --> 00:37:52,201
To rule, there must be love.

675
00:37:52,521 --> 00:37:56,361
Your consent must be pure.

676
00:38:01,081 --> 00:38:05,921
You act out of strategy,
strategy is not consent.

677
00:38:06,841 --> 00:38:08,201
(ALL GROANING)

678
00:38:14,601 --> 00:38:16,641
Do you consent?

679
00:38:16,721 --> 00:38:19,321
I don't have any power. I'm nobody.

680
00:38:19,841 --> 00:38:24,201
You represent the greatest power
on the planet.

681
00:38:24,521 --> 00:38:27,361
You represent the Doctor.

682
00:38:27,961 --> 00:38:31,641
Is your consent pure?

683
00:38:34,601 --> 00:38:36,761
-Is this going to work?
-Trust me.

684
00:38:36,921 --> 00:38:40,561
I pop it in there, machine goes ping,
lab goes boom, world is saved.

685
00:38:40,761 --> 00:38:43,081
You develop
a pretty intense crush on me.

686
00:38:44,081 --> 00:38:46,401
Okay, go through to the machine room.

687
00:38:46,481 --> 00:38:48,601
You're going to have to let me back in
when I'm done.

688
00:38:48,681 --> 00:38:51,241
-How long before the vents kick in?
-Four minutes.

689
00:38:52,841 --> 00:38:53,841
Doctor, are you still there?

690
00:38:53,921 --> 00:38:55,921
There's no way of stopping
the lab venting.

691
00:38:56,001 --> 00:38:58,321
So I'm going to sterilise the building
by blowing it up.

692
00:38:58,401 --> 00:38:59,681
Everything in here will be destroyed.

693
00:38:59,761 --> 00:39:02,441
-Including you?
-Not if I pull my socks up.

694
00:39:02,521 --> 00:39:04,881
Honest answer. You gonna do it?

695
00:39:04,961 --> 00:39:06,081
'Course I'm going to do it.

696
00:39:06,161 --> 00:39:08,921
"Cause... Because
they're still offering a deal, and...

697
00:39:09,561 --> 00:39:10,961
And I'm the only one left.

698
00:39:11,041 --> 00:39:13,001
Tell them you're flattered, but don't.

699
00:39:13,721 --> 00:39:15,881
What does "consent" mean?

700
00:39:17,001 --> 00:39:20,321
You must ask for our help, and want it.

701
00:39:20,401 --> 00:39:23,361
And know you will then be ours.

702
00:39:23,441 --> 00:39:26,641
Only then can the link be formed.

703
00:39:27,601 --> 00:39:28,601
What link?

704
00:39:28,761 --> 00:39:31,521
Do you consent?

705
00:39:34,601 --> 00:39:36,001
(ROOM DECOMPRESSING)

706
00:39:40,961 --> 00:39:42,081
Can you hear me?

707
00:39:44,441 --> 00:39:45,681
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

708
00:39:45,761 --> 00:39:47,801
-I don't even know your name.
-Erica.

709
00:39:51,881 --> 00:39:54,281
Did you always want
to be a scientist, Erica?

710
00:39:54,361 --> 00:39:57,921
Since I was about eight.
Before that I wanted to be a bus driver.

711
00:39:58,001 --> 00:40:00,161
(CHUCKLING) Because I liked
how they waved at other bus drivers.

712
00:40:00,241 --> 00:40:02,321
(BEEPING)

713
00:40:02,721 --> 00:40:04,281
Okay, I've given us two minutes.

714
00:40:04,641 --> 00:40:06,481
Right. You need to get out of there.

715
00:40:08,721 --> 00:40:10,841
(TIMER BEEPING)

716
00:40:21,361 --> 00:40:24,441
Hello, I'm the Doctor.
Saving the world with my eyes shut.

717
00:40:25,161 --> 00:40:26,681
(ALARM RINGING)

718
00:40:38,961 --> 00:40:41,521
Doctor, the clock's going back.
Have you done it?

719
00:40:41,601 --> 00:40:44,281
Yes, I have! I am totally
the President of Earth.

720
00:40:44,361 --> 00:40:46,161
And, from now on, two planes.

721
00:40:46,241 --> 00:40:49,721
One for me, and one for my
glamorous assistant, Erica.

722
00:40:49,801 --> 00:40:53,241
Say hello to the folks at home, Erica.
And let me through the door.

723
00:40:53,321 --> 00:40:55,481
Bill, get the hell out of that pyramid.

724
00:41:03,241 --> 00:41:06,241
I can't open it.
It's under emergency protocol.

725
00:41:06,801 --> 00:41:08,881
You need to use the combination lock.

726
00:41:08,961 --> 00:41:11,241
Set it to three, six, one, four.

727
00:41:19,241 --> 00:41:20,361
Uh...

728
00:41:27,401 --> 00:41:28,561
You're going to have to guide me.

729
00:41:28,641 --> 00:41:30,481
Well, I can't see it from here.

730
00:41:30,561 --> 00:41:31,961
You can see it, right?

731
00:41:32,361 --> 00:41:33,521
How long have I got?

732
00:41:33,601 --> 00:41:37,601
One minute 40. Three, six, one, four.
Come on!

733
00:41:37,681 --> 00:41:39,561
Doctor, what's happening? Are you okay?

734
00:41:39,641 --> 00:41:40,961
Bill, sorry, uh, slight hitch.

735
00:41:41,041 --> 00:41:42,361
-Working on it.
-What's the problem?

736
00:41:42,441 --> 00:41:43,921
Three, six, one, four.
I need to open the door,

737
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:45,321
but I can't, uh, see the numbers.

738
00:41:45,401 --> 00:41:46,521
ERICA: One minute 20.

739
00:41:48,841 --> 00:41:50,121
I don't understand the problem.

740
00:41:50,201 --> 00:41:52,841
Combination lock. All the sonic could
do was calculate the number.

741
00:41:52,921 --> 00:41:54,121
But I still have to enter it.

742
00:41:55,521 --> 00:41:57,921
Nardole. Nardole!

743
00:41:59,201 --> 00:42:00,921
Nardole, I need you to do
a visual on the lab.

744
00:42:01,001 --> 00:42:03,601
There's a camera in here.

745
00:42:04,361 --> 00:42:06,081
Nardole?

746
00:42:07,001 --> 00:42:08,761
Nardole, can you hear me?

747
00:42:09,201 --> 00:42:11,881
I don't understand the problem.
Just open the door.

748
00:42:11,961 --> 00:42:13,801
-I can't.
-Why can't you?

749
00:42:13,881 --> 00:42:14,881
Because I'm blind.

750
00:42:16,561 --> 00:42:18,121
I'm sorry, I'm blind.

751
00:42:19,361 --> 00:42:22,401
(STUTTERING) What do you mean blind,
what are you talking about?

752
00:42:22,641 --> 00:42:26,361
I lied.
I've been blind since Chasm Forge.

753
00:42:26,921 --> 00:42:28,921
I didn't get my sight back,
I've been lying to you.

754
00:42:29,201 --> 00:42:31,641
There's a combination lock,
with numbers, and...

755
00:42:32,961 --> 00:42:34,321
I can't see them.

756
00:42:37,241 --> 00:42:39,721
(CRYING)
You are the stupidest idiot ever.

757
00:42:43,881 --> 00:42:45,521
I'm not gonna let you die.

758
00:42:45,961 --> 00:42:49,001
No, you have to. There's no choice.

759
00:42:49,921 --> 00:42:51,361
No one else can help me now.

760
00:42:51,481 --> 00:42:54,081
The Monks. The Monks can help you.

761
00:42:54,161 --> 00:42:56,321
No. Bill, no. Don't do that.

762
00:42:56,481 --> 00:42:57,801
I'm sorry.

763
00:42:57,881 --> 00:43:00,401
I have made a mistake.
I have to face that.

764
00:43:00,481 --> 00:43:02,241
But do not ask the Monks for help.

765
00:43:02,561 --> 00:43:04,521
(MACHINES BEEPING)

766
00:43:05,801 --> 00:43:06,881
Bill!

767
00:43:08,081 --> 00:43:10,001
Doctor. This planet needs you.

768
00:43:10,361 --> 00:43:13,161
So I'm making an executive decision.

769
00:43:13,881 --> 00:43:15,081
I'm keeping you alive.

770
00:43:15,161 --> 00:43:17,201
Bill. Listen to me. Please.

771
00:43:17,761 --> 00:43:20,361
I don't know what consenting
allows them to do to you.

772
00:43:20,641 --> 00:43:22,721
DOCTOR: You don't know
what you're agreeing to.

773
00:43:23,201 --> 00:43:24,561
Can you give him his sight back?

774
00:43:28,681 --> 00:43:32,081
His sight can be restored.

775
00:43:32,801 --> 00:43:35,281
Then... Then I'm asking you for help.

776
00:43:36,681 --> 00:43:37,801
I give you my consent.

777
00:43:37,881 --> 00:43:40,041
Is your consent pure?

778
00:43:41,441 --> 00:43:43,481
Just give him his sight back.

779
00:43:43,561 --> 00:43:46,161
You can have the world,
just make him see again.

780
00:43:47,481 --> 00:43:49,041
I consent.

781
00:43:56,361 --> 00:43:58,921
You act out of love.

782
00:43:59,641 --> 00:44:02,041
Love is consent.

783
00:44:02,121 --> 00:44:04,401
We must be loved.

784
00:44:04,881 --> 00:44:07,041
Bill, do not make this deal.
I forbid it.

785
00:44:07,121 --> 00:44:08,241
(BEEPING)

786
00:44:10,041 --> 00:44:11,801
Bill, can you hear me? What's happening?

787
00:44:12,241 --> 00:44:13,401
Bill?

788
00:44:14,761 --> 00:44:16,041
Bill?

789
00:44:35,681 --> 00:44:36,681
(DOOR BEEPS)

790
00:44:51,761 --> 00:44:53,481
Bill. What have you done?

791
00:44:55,201 --> 00:44:56,961
Tell you what, old man.

792
00:44:57,641 --> 00:44:59,721
You'd better get my planet back.

793
00:44:59,961 --> 00:45:02,921
MONKS: Enjoy your sight, Doctor.

794
00:45:03,561 --> 00:45:06,361
Now see our world.

795
00:45:07,241 --> 00:45:09,241
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

796
00:45:37,921 --> 00:45:40,041
BILL: 7 woke up,
and the Monks were here.

797
00:45:40,121 --> 00:45:41,241
They've always been here.

798
00:45:41,761 --> 00:45:44,481
All that we believe now is a lie.

799
00:45:44,561 --> 00:45:45,561
I want to speak to her.

800
00:45:45,641 --> 00:45:48,321
All we have to do is find
whoever opened the door to the Monks

801
00:45:48,401 --> 00:45:49,441
and just kill them.

802
00:45:49,521 --> 00:45:52,321
I'm sorry your plus one doesn't get
a happy ending.

803
00:45:53,041 --> 00:45:56,401
All anyone's seen of the Doctor
in the last six months

804
00:45:56,481 --> 00:45:58,001
are those broadcasts he does.

805
00:45:59,721 --> 00:46:00,721
I have joined the Monks.

806
00:46:01,001 --> 00:46:02,001
(GUNSHOT)

